         <abstract>
            <p>The solution of the generalized Abel integral equation &lt;latex&gt;$g(t) = \int^t_0 \{k(t, s)/(t - s)^\alpha\}f(s) ds,\quad 0 &lt; \alpha &lt; 1$&lt;/latex&gt;, where k(t, s) is continuous, by the product integration analogue of the trapezoidal method is examined. It is shown that this method has order two convergence for α ∈ [ α&lt;sub&gt;1&lt;/sub&gt;, 1) with &lt;tex-math&gt;$\alpha_1 \doteqdot 0.2117$&lt;/tex-math&gt;. This interval contains the important case α = 1/2. Convergence of order two for α ∈ (0, α&lt;sub&gt;1&lt;/sub&gt;) is discussed and illustrated numerically. The possibility of constructing higher order methods is illustrated with an example.</p>
          </abstract>
